description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Senior Nursing Assistant&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you motivated, forward thinking and willing to learn new skills?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Can you work autonomously and as part of a team with integrity and enthusiasm?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Would you enjoy the challenge of delivering a new service across the 3 main UHBW sites?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If so then please read on...&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a dynamic and enthusiastic senior nursing assistant to join the newly developed outpatient service, based at the Bristol Haematology and Oncology Centre. The service has been developed to provide phlebotomy, line care and venesections to patients from Bristol and surrounding areas.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate should be enthusiastic and adaptable, and be able to demonstrate compassion and empathy, whilst providing the highest standard of care. Excellent communication skills, both written and verbal are essential for this role, as is the ability to work well within a team. Reliability and dependability is also a key requirement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The position will provide you with a great development opportunity for building new skills. Training and supervision will be provided to help you achieve the required standards, and once fully trained, elements of autonomous work are an expectation of the role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Flexibility with working hours and the ability to travel between the 3 sites is essential in order to effectively deliver the service. (Bristol Haematology &amp; Oncology Centre; South Bristol Community Hospital and North Bristol Concorde Medical Practice)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Clare Pateman&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Clare.pateman@uhbw.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 0117 3421873&lt;/p&gt;
